caption: The service is impeccable, the empanadas are filling and delicious. Plus, they do take and bake so this is a great option if you're not going to eat them right away!

Really loved the empanadas, yes they take some time to arrive after you order but its the kind of place where its nice to slow down and chat with friends for a bit. Aka, clean and casual, nicer than most chains but not stuck up like a lot of places in the city. Staff was incredibly nice. Was happy with both savory and sweet empanada options. Not to mention they make a solid cappuccino. Perks are the proximity to not only public transit but Holiday Jones, pretty perfect if you have out of towners visiting. Great place to grab a bite and some caffeine before a weekend day of exploring the city.

I'm not a huge empanada fan, to be honest. Fried dough pockets remind me a little too much of my destitute 20s spent eating Hot Pockets wishing I had the funds for something that doesn't suck.  However, these do not suck.  To the contrary, these baked and filled wonders are flaky and delicious morsels of South American wonderment. My favorite is the ham and cheese, but you can't go wrong with anything from a mac & cheese to a BBQ chicken or nutella banana and all things in between. They're cooked to order, worth the wait and you can almost pretend they're healthy. Almost.  Plus, sitting in the friendly environs of Wicker Park hostel Holiday Jones makes it feel oddly cosmopolitan to nosh on empanadas whilst drinking coffee and chatting with newfound friends from far fung locales.
